race.comment: COCO JEN (2) resumed off a seven-month spell at Sandown Hillside and ran a very strong race, finding the line well for second behind an in-form horse in Gold Medallist. She did some nice things in her maiden campaign and looks to have come back even better. Up to a mile now suits and she'll take plenty of beating. ENCHANTED JENNI (5) broke through for a strong maiden victory at Sandown Hillside last time out despite doing work in the run, coming clear late in solid time. Straight to a BM66 now but can measure up. Wary of GLOBAL ECLIPSE (3) who resumes having been given a strong chance by the market in a G1 SA Derby before a spell. The six-length maiden win here prior over 2025m was dominant and he can return with a good run. STREET LARK (6) can sneak a placing.
